Every park is a labyrinth. Every park has a centre, even if you have not discovered it yet. Just as the heart is the centre of man, but is not in the exact middle, so the centre of the labyrinth (park) is not in its exact middle.

You are walking through a park with someone, talking. Your conversation depends on the path you take, if you took a different path, you will lead a different conversation. If you walk an unusual route, you will have an unusual conversation. Every conversation changes your life.

So every route you take maps to a different conversation, at every crossroads you choose your life, no? There is a route, that you have not walked, that will bring immense riches to you, or torture and death. Left or right? Look at this tree, how nice it is... what was I saying?

Maybe the centre of the park is not a place, it is a certain unusual route, that will allow you to see with new eyes, new perspective. How many routes can you take? A few hundred, at least. That's a few hundred conversations, few hundred thoughts if alone. Which one is the heart?
